## Logging Configuration

Set up logging levels and outputs in the logging.json file:

json
{
  "version": 1,
  "formatters": {
    "simple": {
      "format": "%(asctime)s - %(name)s - %(levelname)s - %(message)s"
    }
  },
  "handlers": {
    "console": {
      "class": "logging.StreamHandler",
      "formatter": "simple"
    }
  },
  "root": {
    "level": "INFO",
    "handlers": ["console"]
  }
}


This setup logs to console by default.

### JavaScript Functions

Functions encapsulate reusable code:

javascript
function greet(name) {
  return `Hello, ${name}!`;
}

console.log(greet("Alice")); // Hello, Alice!


Pass arguments to customize behavior dynamically.

### Binary Search Algorithm

Binary search finds elements in sorted arrays efficiently.

Pseudocode:

function binarySearch(arr, target):
    low = 0
    high = len(arr) - 1
    while low <= high:
        mid = (low + high) // 2
        if arr[mid] == target:
            return mid
        elif arr[mid] < target:
            low = mid + 1
        else:
            high = mid - 1
    return -1


Time complexity: O(log n).
